      "id": "searchb_question_wildcard_in_kanji",
      "formula": "=SEARCHB(\"?\", \"漢ABC\")",
      "setup": {},
      "skipped": "SEARCHB's '?' wildcard in Mac Excel ja-JP matches a single SBCS byte rather than a UTF-8 codepoint, so =SEARCHB(\"?\",\"漢ABC\") returns 3 (the 'A' position) because '?' refuses to match the 2-byte kanji. Formulon's wildcard_find treats '?' uniformly as one codepoint (returning 1) and is shared with SEARCH; mirroring Mac would require a byte-mode wildcard matcher dedicated to SEARCHB."
